  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Write a program to find the median of two sorted arrays of same size.\n\nFor example:\n\nThe given array ->1 is : 1 5 13 24 35\n\nThe given array ->2 is : 3 8 15 17 32\n\nThe median of the 2 sorted arrays is :14\n\nExplanation:\n\nAfter merging two arrays,we get 1 3 5 8 13 15 17 24 32 35\n\nIn the middle two elements are 13 & 15.\n\nAverage of these two is (13+15)/2=14\n\nHence median of these two array is 14.",
    "constraints": [
      "1<=N<=100",
      "0<=arr[i]<=10^6"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The first line has an integer N denotes the size, which is same for both the array.\n\nThe second line contains N values separated by space",
    "outputFormat": "Print the median",
